<br>
I'll leave the specifics for Lagdalen and Flarren, but I will recap what I saw, or at least recall seeing...<br>
<br>
No clue when we got things started, though people started to assemble around 6pm MST.  Not sure on exact numbers, though based on the cash I got to hold on to...there were 44 people on the raid...minus the Valoran group, which was 5...2 in that group may have been included with the raiding group...i know there was a 51 rogue in the CR group.<br>
<br>
Discipline was far better this time.  I didn't see any gates opening or people continuously crossing points that they weren't supposed to.  I corrected one person once...he got confused because the Valoran guys went ahead through the doors...thought we were all supposed to go...gave a polite tell and the problem was solved.  Outside some emote spamming/drinking/mild chat items, discipline couldn't have been much better.<br>
<br>
Execution was probably the reason we lost.  I didn't get to witness all of it...went LD at the 60% mark, but from the reports I heard, the Healers didn't do quite what they were supposed to, nor did the tanks give the healers fair warning.  No one really to blame for this, nor would there be reason to blame anyone for it if there were.  Something to stew over next raid so it doesn't happen again.  Guestimates were we had her down to the L in Lady Vox...that's about 5-10% folks...we almost nailed her.<br>
<br>
Next time be sure to have a hot button /shouting that you need a heal (for the tanks) and that the healers make sure that person gets healed.  For all intents and purposes don't pay attention to the red bars in your group...look for the red text and get that tank back in.<br>
<br>
I honestly think we could have taken her down in a 2nd attempt...we had the man (and woman) power to take her out...just missed the first go.  Had the timing been better (ie not been 1-day notice) we would have won.  Too many people had to go, or we probably would have made a 2nd attempt.<br>
<br>
We improved leaps and bounds since the last raid...some minor flaws in communication were about the only hitches...definately something that won't hold us back long...I have a feeling we'll have a nice streak of dragon victories in the future <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Final notes:  I can't begin to thank Valoran for donating thier time to the raid.  Ashavir, Ogun, and Madori especially for the pulling before and Corpse pulling after...as well as Ogun's rez stick...that saved us god knows how much time.  It was a pleasure working with them.  <br>
<br>
I don't know if you guys know...but during the buffing line I very well could have killed everyone, or at least that's what it felt like distance wise.  While everyone was buffing, I was in Vox's lair pulling the giants out...at one point I got feared down almost to the bottom of the first ramp...had Vox not hit me as hard as she did, I may have pulled her into summoning range and that would not have been good at all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .  Kudos to whatever god was watching over us.  I don't know if that's a normallity...but it was a pretty sketch moment for me...I was expecting 40 very pissed off people /tell spamming me for ruining the raid about 2 minutes after I popped back in Thurgadin (was bound there)...glad everyone at least got to see her.<br>
<br>
Corpse Recovery went pretty smoothly...wish i would have been rezzed earlier so I could have helped earlier...but that's how it works...no one to blame for it and no reason to do so anyway...I got to play Ollie Ollie Oxen Free with Vox a time or two...ran to the hallway behind her throne and rezzed (poor man's CoH as Ogun put it...hehe)to an intentional corpse in the hallway so the Valoran guys could pull bodies from under her.  Not sure how well the strategy worked...but it sure was a lot of fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Three cheers for Valoran...if Karma does exist, these guys are in for a real treat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Good raid you guys...we'll nail her next time. <p>Good Journies,<BR>
Stonescale Thulefist<BR>
Nikyu of the Swifttail Caste<BR>
GL, Peacekeepers of Norrath<BR>
