<br>
One thing I will add is in regards to how we handled buffing.  Don't get me wrong, I think the Valoran folks did an amazing job and getting in there was so much faster and easier than ever before - especially given how late we got started, they were a big part of how smoothly the raid went.  I can't begin to thank them enough.<br>
<br>
When it came time to do buffing, however... I think part of the reason we lost is that there basically weren't enough buffs in front of our CR and MR:  My resistances got dispelled considerably earlier than usual, and the mass-dying of tanks happened noticable earlier than I remember happening on previous successes.  Had there been fewer tanks dead so soon, fewer people feared so early because the MR buff lasted longer... I think we would have popped her easily.  Also, the addition of a rune, as well as DMF (which is very hard to dispell, and really should be in front of the CR buff, not last as usual) would have helped tank survival a little more - probably enough for a win.  We had her down to the beginning of the 'L' in 'Lady Vox' - that's in the 1000hp left range... we were damned close.<br>
<br>
Another factor was basically luck... Vox has a number of healing spells she casts - Greater, Superior, and Complete.  I've gone through entire raids and seen her cast nothing but GH and SH, &quot;Lady Vox feels much better.&quot;   Tonight she went for CH's... but even with that we would have nailed her with just a little bit more damage to push us over the top. <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueqkommisar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqkommisar</A> at: 6/7/01 9:39:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>King and Queen of Lag</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/7/01 12:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Recap </span><hr size=1> Thnx for starting in on the thread. I've been sent home sick from work today cause of no sleep last night and was so dead I didn't get to start one last night.<br>
<br>
Started out slow, comes with only 1 days warning and for that I'm sorry to those of you that are not used to CoG and its methods of movement.<br>
<br>
Getting in was quick, IG's were dispatched in record time by Valoran and buff line was completed rather quickly. Good job all for keeping eyes up for messages.<br>
<br>
Reason we didn't have DMF last night was cause there were no necro's, and next time we'll be sure to throw on a few crappy personal buffs too. Other than that buff line went very well.<br>
<br>
As to listening. I have never been more impressed. In the chat room everyone sat and listened to the directions and asked questions at the end. Good job! That made my life alot easier and got us back in alot faster.<br>
<br>
Got ready, tanks up to the ramp, clerics to the back of them and called the attack after a confirmation from all groups. No hesitation this time, everyone was ready to kill. Her life began dropping regularily fast as the progressive waves were called in. My first death was at about 30% after unloading into her tummy. I had taken a trip out to the triage line but there seemed to be no healers there (I might be blind) it all looked like a mess of tanks just standing there. Healers where were you? I got kinda confused then. I got a mini heal from a paladin I believe and ran back in to see her at about that 30% which is when she got me. Progressively with my 7 deaths she kept loosing life. Scared she would CH, I ran in to unload as fast as I could along with everyone else. Just before my last death I was standing under her with less than half an L left in her name and the worst thing ever happened. Vox began casting and then her life went up. I was promptly feared and just before being killed by her AE managed to call the Back Off.<br>
<br>
Talk about depressing. She was under 10% for about 5 or 6 of my deaths but just couldn't put the dmg into her fast enough.<br>
We were close though. SO close.<br>
<br>
Big thank you too all those that attended (as you've noticed I have tried to skip the godawful nasty parts of which there weren't any really and stay positive about it) The promptness of the group leaders was great on reports, movements were controlled and Valoran, we owe you again.<br>
<br>
C ya all in a few days when Naggy is up.<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho -Fellowship of Faydark-<br>
lvl 52 Elementalist Officer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/7/01 1:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Recap</span><hr size=1> I was personally impressed by the fact that we were even able to attempt Vox.  Many other alliances and guilds would have passed in the same situation.  No matter how Uber you are, if your people are not online, you can do squat.  We were still able to muster 45 people on extremely short notice.  Under 6 hours I believe.  Considering we are sort of limited to people between levels 40 and 52, thats amazing.  Made even more so since many of the CoG guilds and friends were busy with their own alliances that night.  CoK and AoVB were on Hate and Fear respectively.  We were shorter than a gnome thats been cut off at the knees in fact.  But we still managed to muster a raid.<br>
<br>
Our discipline was tight all night.  No other word for it.  There were a few problems with emotes and spamming, but that was quickly cleared up, and not repeated.  That was good.  I have no problems with people making an honest mistake or not understanding something.  Once.  After the rules were explained, it didnt recurr.  That is how its supposed to happen.  Even in the chat room things were very orderly and organized.  No one inturrpted Lag when she was giving instructions.  That was a good thing.<br>
<br>
The buff line went quickly and very orderly.  When it was time to go, people did not wander into the pits and other ramps.  We went in when told and the waves did their job.  Vox did not move till the very end, and that wasnt really anyone's fault.  With the lack of tanks to hold her to the wall, and casters getting feared left and right, there wasnt anything else we could do.<br>
<br>
Healing.  This seems to be a major problem.  On the other hand, we only had, I believe, 1 cleric.  Besides Ogun who cant help during the raid.  And I think 3 shammies.  That was it for the healers, since druids were ordered in to nuke.  Now, I'm not saying that we had any other choice.  We had to go with what we had, which was 1 cleric.  Also a druid sub 51 isnt much good for healing a tank, or even a buffed caster.  Gheal just doesnt cut it on raids like this.  And between 51-52 a druid can land nukes effectively on Vox.  I know I did about 5k or so damage on her, maybe more.  I only got 1 partial resist, no full resists, and emptied my mana bar twice.  So I cant say I would've been more effective healing.  Especially considering how light we were in nukers of the appropriate levels.  But I believe that was why we had such a hard time healing the tanks.  I dont see how we could have done anything differently tho, except maybe find more clerics next time.  We simply had too few of everything and had to make the best with what we had.<br>
<br>
I know the KGC rules can be messed up at times.  But look at it this way.  In spite of the lack of time and forewarning, despite the fact we were unable to trade with another guild, despite the fact we had even fewer than usual numbers to draw on, we still were able to muster and make the attempt.  Call it what you will, I say we succeded.  And Naggy had better look out.  We've got some serious revenge to take out.<br>
<br>
You did a great job with what you had Lagdalen and Flarren.  I wish it could've been more and I wish we could've taken her.  But we had enough to try, and we failed not through lack of effort or leadership, but in the end more to bad luck and some bad resists than anything else.  We gave our best with no holding back and we should all be proud of that.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Druid, 52, Very Edible<br>
Still seeking the secret breeding grounds of the Swedish Bikini Team. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Pippified Lizard King</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/7/01 1:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Recap </span><hr size=1> Since everyone else has covered most of the raid from a tanks perspective, let me tell you from a Healer's perspective.  I thought things were going great as the first wave went in, then as the second wave went in some of the first wave were oming back for heals.<br>
<br>
I went on a complete mana burn at that point.  I could not cast fast enough.  I had particle effects and spell messages turned off, so I can't say what the other healers were doing. Had I not remembered that I had those options off, I would have been screaming my lungs out since I saw no one healing except me.<br>
<br>
I had tanks screaming for heals, and all I could do was &quot;/shout OOM, and heading towards Vox&quot; (or something like that).  Never imagined I would be running like my head was on fire straight into Vox's face!  And to top it off, I got to Vox and hit Attack.  I also managed to squeeze off 2 Cannibalize II's and unload a Shock of the Tainted.... Resist.  But it got her attention as she finally turned to me and said, &quot;Stupid Iksar.  Die.&quot;   And I did... finally.  <br>
<br>
After my 3rd death Vox was still showing only about 5% life left, but I saw no one in the lair. Not a soul.  Every tanks was dead by that point, and the casters were no where to be seen.  Reason?  All the casters had just ran from the lair screaming their heads off like all the demons of hell were chasing them.<br>
<br>
There was speculation that we did not have enough healers without the druids.  I don't know what number of healers we had, but using the druids as nukers was a good idea.  Maybe keeping a couple back as healers could have been the edge we needed.<br>
<br>
All in all, this raid went so well that I am surprised we did not take her down.  I am very happy that Valoran cleared the way to the lair for us, and then continued to help out with buffs and CR.<br>
<br>
Stonescale did not mention it, so I will.  The Peacekeepers had an astonishing 6 people at the raid.  In over 2 years we have not managed that, so this raid was a milestone for us.  Also, Stonescale related to me how honored he felt to be chosen as Loot Master and to be a puller.  I was honored and anxious to be chosen as a group leader (you should have warned me Lagdalen!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
One last item..... Someone related to me that she felt a bit abused last night at the raid.  She did not fit the typical role for her class at a Vox raid, but she put her life on the line just as everyone else did.  She related that several people told her she was useless.  She knew that she did not fit the typical role, but that is beside the point.  If I ever hear someone telling someone else they are usless on a raid while that person is giving it their all, you can bet there will be hell to pay. <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulenenaemcgillicuddy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenenae McGillicuddy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/7/01 3:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/lenmug.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Recap </span><hr size=1> I stopped reading after the first part about healers not healing fast enough. Suggestion, next time take more healers. Might of been a good idea to have any 51/52 druids stay out and heal instead of nuke, if we had any with us.<br>
<br>
I don't think it was a problem with shouting, problem was we can only cast so fast. I know I was casting constantly, it's times like that, that I wish I had been a high-elf.<br>
<br>
I think it was my sorry level 50 self and one other 49 cleric covering 3 groups screaming for heals.<br>
<br>
