d not do anything about.  Vox spawned very unexpectedly.  We had something like 6 hours to find enough people and prep for the raid.  So its not surprising we came up short.  And we did very good when you take all that into account.<br>
<br>
And I am simply appalled that anyone could tell someone else on the raid that they were useless.  We didnt have enough people at some occasions to attempt to clear the IG's without help.  We had to scrape the bottom to find people, and I for one was very grateful for those who did choose to come along even tho conventional wisdom says they're &quot;useless&quot;.  No one on a CoG raid is useless.  And all joking aside, everyone including myself, do contribute more to a raid than just lag.  If nothing else they may provide suicidal cannon fodder or an extra small heal or a few low nukes that might save the day.  You dont know.  And even if all they can bring is a joke and a good attitude, thats worth it in my book.  I'd rather have a lowbie with crappy equipment who has a good attitude and a few jokes along than a lvl 52 warrior in full cobalt wielding his epics that is condesending.  Not only can we not afford to be picky, last night was a prime example, but CoG really exists for the little guys.  The people who would not normally get into raids or large targets.  All I can say is that whoever made those comments is lucky I didnt find out and unload on them, and they're doubly lucky with sugar on it that Lag didnt find out or I can gaurantee that she would've made them wish they were somewhere safe like a PvP server or something.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Druid, 52, Edible<br>
